  <span id="freeText2320606895539663834" style="display:none">3.25 ⭐️<br /><br />A mixed read for me. Story was well-written, plot was complex and perhaps a tad too emotional/heavy for me. I enjoyed reading the book initially but at mid-point I was struggling to finish it. The book was written with Sophie’s POV. I normally do not have any issues with book written in 1st person but this felt a little too one-sided; too many monologues. To compound it, there weren’t that many interactions or scenes between the 2 MCs and other secondary characters. Ian featured way too often - too many times that it almost felt like he was one of the main characters. Well, that’s just my take on the story. I’m just not ‘getting into the grove’ with the story - much to my chagrin.</span>
