<div id="review_2292410862" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2292410862" />
    <a title="Completely Melanie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43827854-completely-melanie"><img alt="Completely Melanie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514821962p2/43827854.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2292410862?book_show_action=true">Feb 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Completely Melanie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Completely Melanie" href="/user/show/43827854-completely-melanie">Completely Melanie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook " href="/book/show/31677792-in-the-distance-there-is-light">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/43827854-completely-melanie?shelf=unhauled">unhauled</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2292410862" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12954619285610418507">This is an LGBTQ+ love story about two women who fall in love after losing a man they both love. I listened to the audio book for this. This book made me very uncomfortable listening to it, and it had nothing to do with the romance between two women. I have no issue with that. The issue that I had was who these 2 women were to each other prior to the relationship that made this so uncomfortable. Here&apos;s a quick back story of who Sophie and Delores were to each other prior to their relationship:<br/><br/>1.</span>
  <span id="freeText12954619285610418507" style="display:none">This is an LGBTQ+ love story about two women who fall in love after losing a man they both love. I listened to the audio book for this. This book made me very uncomfortable listening to it, and it had nothing to do with the romance between two women. I have no issue with that. The issue that I had was who these 2 women were to each other prior to the relationship that made this so uncomfortable. Here's a quick back story of who Sophie and Delores were to each other prior to their relationship:<br /><br />1. Ian's biological mother was a lesbian. When Ian was 5 years old Delores entered their lives. Delores was Ian's mother's life partner. Ian considered both of them as his mothers. Present day Ian's biological mother died from Cancer some years back.<br /><br />2. Sophie and Ian are a straight couple. They are in love, but decided against marriage as a way to honor his mother because his mother wasn't allowed to marry the person that she loved (Delores). Sophie and Ian live together and have been a couple for 5 years. <br /><br />3. Ian is involved in an accident and dies instantly. Sophie (who is 30) and Delores (who is 56) are both mourning for Ian, and they find comfort in each other. That comfort turns into a hot steamy romance.<br /><br />So essentially she is doing her dead boyfriend's mom. That just seemed wrong on so many levels. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12954619285610418507" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


